description: Neste repositrio so apresentadas tcnicas avanadas  exibindo o potencial ilimitado de algoritmos de Machine Learning, envolvendo modelos de Deep Learning e outras tcnicas do estado-da-arte, tcnicas de aprendizado supervisionado e no supervisionado, modelos implementados em Python e R, os principais frameworks e bibliotecas.

The project streamlines job searching by using NLP and web scraping to extract skills from resumes and fetch job opportunities from Naukri.com. Machine learning improves job matching accuracy, offering a personalized job-hunting experience. Technologies include NLP libraries, ML frameworks, and Selenium.

This repository contains code for deploying machine learning models as APIs using FastAPI. FastAPI is a modern, fast (high-performance) web framework for building APIs with Python 3.7+ based on standard Python type hints.

mlinoe (machine learning in observables explanation) is a python package that provides a framework to compare a collection of physical models and select the model that is more likely to reproduce the experimental constraints.
Projects of the machine learning frameworks aimed at multi-fidelity.

DeepAIKit is an open-source library developed entirely from scratch to provide comprehensive tools for machine learning and deep learning. Without relying on existing frameworks like scikit-learn, PyTorch, or TensorFlow, DeepAIKit simplifies the development, training, and deployment of ML and DL models.

The Background Eraser Flask App is a web application designed to provide a simple and efficient way for users to remove the background from their images. Built using Flask, web application framework in Python, this app leverages advanced machine learning models to accurately and quickly perform background removal on uploaded images.

A machine learning project to develop virtual creatures capable of climbing a mountain. This project includes the basic framework, movement simulation, and fitness evaluation to iteratively improve the creature's climbing abilities.

Jupyter is an open-source platform in Python, essential for machine and deep learning. It provides interactive notebooks that integrate code, equations, and visualizations. Jupyter supports frameworks like TensorFlow and PyTorch, facilitating experimentation, debugging, and documentation, crucial for developing AI models.

The project is made using Django framework(python).

Moe-KAN integrates KolmogorovArnold Networks (KANs) into a Mixture of Experts (MoE) framework, enhancing efficiency and performance. Inspired by a suggestion from Frazer on Discord, this project combines the strengths of MoE and KANs for advanced machine learning tasks.

This project aims to provide outfit recommendations based on user input for weather conditions and color preferences. The core functionality is powered by a K-Nearest Neighbors (KNN) machine learning model implemented in Python using the Flask framework.
